   "body" : "This PR defines two new service bits `NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED` according to the BIP draft (https://github.com/jonasschnelli/bips/wiki/NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED-BIP-DRAFT).\r\n\r\n\r\n### Signaling\r\n* Pruned peers with at least 144+144 blocks available will signal `NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED_LOW` (regardless of the tip time, same as `NODE_NETWORK`)\r\n* Pruned peers with at least 144*7+144 blocks available will signal `NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED_HIGH`\r\n* Pruned peers with at least 144*(7^2)+144 blocks available will signal `NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED_HIGH & NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED_LOW`\r\n\r\nOnce a new block got connected, the flags may change.\r\n\r\n### Address Relay\r\nPeers will relay addresses that matches only `NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED_LOW` or `NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED_HIGH` .\r\n\r\n### Connecting\r\nPeers no longer in IBD may connect to `NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED_LOW` after 10 failed attempts and with at least a fourth of the outbound connections up.",
